            <listPerson>
                <person xml:id="saint-320" ana="#syriaca-saint">
                    <persName xml:id="name320-1" xml:lang="syr" syriaca-tags="#syriaca-headword" source="#bib320-1">ܐܒܪܗܡ ܟܫܟܪܝܐ</persName>
                    <persName xml:id="name320-2" xml:lang="en-x-gedsh" syriaca-tags="#syriaca-headword">Abraham Kashkaraya</persName>
                    <persName xml:id="name320-3" xml:lang="syr" source="#bib320-1">ܐܒܪܗܡ</persName>
                    <persName xml:id="name320-4" xml:lang="en">Abraham of Kashkar</persName>
                    <persName xml:id="name320-5" xml:lang="en">Abraham of Kashkar, Abraham the Great</persName>
                    <persName xml:id="name320-6" xml:lang="fr-x-zanetti" source="#bib320-1">ʾAḇrāhām Kaškarāyā</persName>
                    <persName xml:id="name320-7" xml:lang="fr-x-zanetti" source="#bib320-1">ʾAḇrāhām</persName>
                    <persName xml:id="name320-8" xml:lang="fr" source="#bib320-1">Abraham de Kashkar</persName>
                    <persName xml:id="name320-9" xml:lang="fr-x-fiey" source="#bib320-2">ABRAHAM DE KAŜKAR</persName>
                    <idno type="URI">http://syriaca.org/person/320</idno>
                    <idno type="FIEY">23</idno>
                    <idno type="BHS">982</idno>
                    <idno type="BHS">981</idno>
                    <sex value="M" source="#bib320-2">male</sex>
                    <birth when="0492" syriaca-computed-start="0492-01-01" source="#bib320-2">0492</birth>
                    <death when="0586" syriaca-computed-start="0586-01-01" source="#bib320-2">0586</death>
                    <state type="martyr" source="#bib320-2">
                        <p>Martyr</p>
                    </state>
                    <note>Fiey provides the following bibliographic citations: <quote source="#bib320-2">La commemoraison d' Abraham etait le 2 mai chez les Syriaques orientaux.
Les sources primitives de Ia Vie d'Abraham (Abba Jean et R.abban Rustam) sont
perdues, mais ont ete utilisees par Je Liber castitatis ; par Thomas de Marga,
Liber superiorum, I.4 ; par MarT ibn Sulayman, 47 arabe ; par Ia Chronique de
Seert, II, 41-43 ; par sa Vita editee par Sachau (BHO, 14) ; et par J'Histoire de
Rabban bar 'Idta (ROC 11 [1906], 406-408).
Ses regles ont ete editees en syriaque et traduites en anglais par V66bus, Documents,
150- 62.
Resume dans DHGE, I, col. 174- 75.
BSO, I, 26- 28 (J. Rabbi).</quote>
                    </note>
                    <note type="abstract">Abraham Kashkaraya (Abraham the Great of Kashkar, or "the elder") was a celebrated reformer of monasticism in Mesopotamia and a great saint of the Church of the East. A student of the School of Nisibis, Abraham was a missionary, ascetic, and miracle-worker. He was called "Father of the Monks of the Orient."</note>
                    <note type="disambiguation">goes with sergius</note>
                    <bibl xml:id="bib320-1">
                        <title level="m" xml:lang="la">Bibliotheca Hagiographica Syriaca</title>
                        <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/bibl/649"/>
                        <citedRange unit="entry">982, 981</citedRange>
                    </bibl>
                    <bibl xml:id="bib320-2">
                        <title level="m" xml:lang="fr">Saints Syriaques</title>
                        <title level="a" xml:lang="fr">ABRAHAM DE KAŜKAR</title>
                        <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/bibl/650"/>
                        <citedRange unit="entry">23</citedRange>
                    </bibl>
                    <note>The commemoration of Abraham was May 2 among the East Syrians.</note>
                    <note>Earliest sources of the Life of Abraham (Abba John and Rabban Rustam) are lost, but they were used by the following:</note>
                    <bibl xml:id="bib320-5">
                        <title>Liber Castatis </title>
                    </bibl>
                    <bibl xml:id="bib320-6">
                        <author>Thomas of Marga</author>
                        <title>Liber superiorum</title>
                        <citedRange>I.4</citedRange>
                    </bibl>
                    <bibl xml:id="bib320-7">
                        <author>Mārī ibn Sulaymān</author>
                        <citedRange>47 arabe</citedRange>
                    </bibl>
                    <bibl xml:id="bib320-8">
                        <title>Chronicle of Seert</title>
                        <citedRange>II, 41-43</citedRange>
                    </bibl>
                    <bibl xml:id="bib320-9">
                        <title>Vita</title>
                        <title>BHO</title>
                        <editor>Sachau</editor>
                        <citedRange>BHO 14</citedRange>
                    </bibl>
                    <bibl xml:id="bib320-10">
                        <title>History of Rabban bar 'Idta</title>
                        <citedRange>ROC 11 [1906], 406-408</citedRange>
                    </bibl>
                    <bibl xml:id="bib320-11">
                        <note>His rules were edited in Syriac and translated into English</note>
                        <editor>Vööbus</editor>
                        <title>Syriac and Arabic Documents Regarding Legislation Relative to Syrian Asceticism</title>
                        <citedRange>1960, 150-62</citedRange>
                    </bibl>
                    <bibl xml:id="bib320-12">
                        <note>Summary in</note>
                        <title>DHGE</title>
                        <citedRange>I, col. 174-75</citedRange>
                    </bibl>
